WEBVTT

00:04.560 --> 00:05.680
You're my man on the inside.

00:05.800 --> 00:06.840
Sooner or later,
these protesters

00:06.960 --> 00:07.960
are gonna start
breaking the law,

00:08.080 --> 00:09.600
and I wanna know before they do.

00:09.720 --> 00:10.640
Men are pigs.

00:10.760 --> 00:12.440
No way am I ever
getting married.

00:12.560 --> 00:13.680
Come on, love.

00:13.800 --> 00:15.280
You know you really want me.

00:15.400 --> 00:16.520
No, I don't.

00:16.640 --> 00:19.480
I need someone to
be attracted to me.

00:19.600 --> 00:22.560
OK, is it just me, or areyour wives also acting weird.

00:22.680 --> 00:23.480
Rita's fine.

00:23.600 --> 00:24.520
Thank God for rugby, I say.

00:28.040 --> 00:29.120
They called the game off.

00:29.240 --> 00:30.000
It's about Mammy.

00:32.680 --> 00:35.040
[music - toy love, "rebel"]

00:38.160 --> 00:42.000
[SINGING] His teeth as hesmiles are white and glistening.

00:42.120 --> 00:46.960
He don't know the name ofthe song he's whistling.

00:47.080 --> 00:50.920
He says what he likes,'cause nobody's listening.

00:51.040 --> 00:53.880
He's a mod, and he's a rebel.

00:54.000 --> 00:57.360
Lives so high 'cause he knowshe'll never find his level.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.120
Did Mrs. O'Driscoll
die of natural causes?

01:03.240 --> 01:04.360
Yes, love.

01:04.480 --> 01:05.520
Can I come to the funeral?

01:05.640 --> 01:07.520
No, love.

01:10.200 --> 01:12.000
If they're not
final, then bin them.

01:12.120 --> 01:13.600
And of course, there's this.

01:22.240 --> 01:25.280
We've got a funeral to get to.

01:25.400 --> 01:26.320
Can I come to the funeral?

01:26.440 --> 01:27.240
No.

01:49.720 --> 01:57.880
Phin, sweetie, almost there.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.320
Well done.

02:00.440 --> 02:01.520
Stop hogging the paper.

02:01.640 --> 02:03.760
I need to know
about Lady Di's dress.

02:03.880 --> 02:06.040
"The dress by David
and Elizabeth Emanuel

02:06.160 --> 02:08.040
remains a closely
guarded secret."

02:08.160 --> 02:10.360
What's a man doing
designing a dress?

02:10.480 --> 02:12.920
Must be a puff.
- Dad, they're married.

02:13.040 --> 02:13.920
So?

02:14.040 --> 02:15.000
When did that ever stop anyone.

02:15.120 --> 02:16.320
You're married.

02:16.440 --> 02:17.520
- But I'm not a puff, am I?- Hurry up.

02:17.640 --> 02:19.080
You don't wanna be
late for school.

02:19.200 --> 02:20.960
Listen to your mother.

02:21.080 --> 02:23.200
Anyway, what does isit matter what she wears?

02:23.320 --> 02:24.360
CHELSEA: It's her wedding day.

02:24.480 --> 02:25.840
Of course, it matters.

02:25.960 --> 02:27.440
Wedding days are forever.

02:27.560 --> 02:30.280
I said, hurry up, go.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.680
It's not gonna be the full,bloody Catholic number, is it?

02:32.800 --> 02:35.960
I have no idea, Lefty.

02:36.080 --> 02:37.000
So have you got enough change?

02:37.120 --> 02:38.640
All present and great.

02:38.760 --> 02:40.360
Right, see if you canunload some of these lemons

02:40.480 --> 02:42.040
while everyone's caught
up in the romance.

02:42.160 --> 02:44.240
Aw, they're works
of art, these are.

02:44.360 --> 02:46.800
Shame you spelled
Diana with two N's.

02:46.920 --> 02:50.440
Oh, she's a slice ofgorgeous, however you spell it.

02:50.560 --> 02:53.840
Oh, and that snap of hairand that see-through frock.

02:53.960 --> 02:55.640
Do you think she'll keep itup with the wedding dress?

02:58.320 --> 02:59.080
Hello.

03:05.000 --> 03:05.760
Get out.

03:09.800 --> 03:10.600
There's something I need--

03:10.720 --> 03:11.640
I said, get out.

03:16.160 --> 03:17.200
Who's that lady?

03:19.800 --> 03:20.600
She's no one.

03:25.520 --> 03:26.840
You have to stop this.

03:26.960 --> 03:29.360
You're making your father angry.

03:29.480 --> 03:31.800
FATHER: Rita, inside!

03:37.280 --> 03:39.960
She's no one at all.

03:40.080 --> 03:40.920
[theme music]

03:41.040 --> 03:41.840
THEME SONG: Watch your back.

03:41.960 --> 03:43.000
Watch your back.

03:43.120 --> 03:45.320
When you're walking
down the alleys.

03:45.440 --> 03:46.320
Watch your back.

03:46.440 --> 03:47.320
Watch your back.

03:47.440 --> 03:50.800
When you're out on the street.

03:50.920 --> 03:53.280
And there's a strangeron the street these days.

03:53.400 --> 03:56.240
You can't see it through
the fog and haze.

03:56.360 --> 03:58.720
Well, everybody's going crazy.

03:58.840 --> 04:00.480
Everybody's going crazy.

04:00.600 --> 04:03.320
Everybody's going crazy.

04:11.200 --> 04:14.000
No shit.

04:14.120 --> 04:16.040
Thank you.

04:16.160 --> 04:17.280
I could come with you.

04:17.400 --> 04:18.200
No, you couldn't.

04:18.320 --> 04:20.560
I could be your date.

04:20.680 --> 04:22.000
It's a funeral.

04:22.120 --> 04:23.520
You can take a
date to a funeral.

04:23.640 --> 04:24.800
Not me.

04:24.920 --> 04:25.920
Not you.

04:26.040 --> 04:27.960
And certainly not
to this funeral.

04:28.080 --> 04:29.560
Don't you want
your gang to meet

04:29.680 --> 04:31.920
this dolly bird you've beenginning off to Sydney with?

04:32.040 --> 04:33.400
Not when the dollybird's you.

04:33.520 --> 04:35.360
You know, for a
career criminal,

04:35.480 --> 04:38.360
you're not very daring.

04:38.480 --> 04:40.560
Which is why I
still have a career.

04:43.680 --> 04:47.480
Phineas, he's the brooding,angry one with mother issues,

04:47.600 --> 04:48.760
right?
- Hm.

04:48.880 --> 04:50.160
Dead mother issues now.

04:50.280 --> 04:52.320
Oh, he sounds complex.

04:52.440 --> 04:53.200
He isn't.

04:53.320 --> 04:56.240
I wanna meet him.

04:56.360 --> 04:57.320
He's not ready to meet you.

05:00.440 --> 05:04.920
There's no way I
can change your mind?

05:05.040 --> 05:06.200
No, no.

05:06.320 --> 05:10.200
Steve, you're not
coming to the funeral,

05:10.320 --> 05:13.560
and you're never
meeting these guys.

05:13.680 --> 05:14.920
Are you ashamed of me?

05:15.040 --> 05:17.560
No.

05:17.680 --> 05:20.000
I just know they're not ready.

05:20.120 --> 05:21.600
They never will be.

05:21.720 --> 05:27.480
Is it OK to break the
law for a higher good?

05:27.600 --> 05:30.000
Every time someone
asks that question,

05:30.120 --> 05:31.440
or when I found
myself in a position

05:31.560 --> 05:34.600
where I might be about
to break the law,

05:34.720 --> 05:38.280
I ask myself, what would
Blair Peach have done?

05:43.920 --> 05:45.520
You haven't changed your mind?

05:45.640 --> 05:46.480
I can't.

05:46.600 --> 05:48.200
I gotta go to that funeral.

05:48.320 --> 05:50.440
This one's actually deceased?

05:50.560 --> 05:51.840
Yeah, my friend's mum.

05:51.960 --> 05:54.360
You know, he'll be
taking it real hard.

05:54.480 --> 05:55.760
[speaking maori]

05:58.520 --> 06:00.320
That's "I'm sorry"
in our language.

06:00.440 --> 06:03.000
Oh, you said that real nice.

06:03.120 --> 06:04.880
And I'll look for
you on the news.

06:05.000 --> 06:06.520
We'll be the ones atthe South African embassy.

06:06.640 --> 06:07.720
Oh, good luck, eh.

06:07.840 --> 06:09.280
It's just another march.

06:09.400 --> 06:10.920
I mean flying
down to Wellington.

06:11.040 --> 06:13.840
I hear the landings arereal mean if it's blowing.

06:13.960 --> 06:14.720
I'm sure we'll be fine.

06:18.840 --> 06:20.400
That's where I'm staying.

06:20.520 --> 06:21.520
If you wanna call me.

06:24.480 --> 06:26.000
[speaking maori]

06:35.600 --> 06:38.120
Do we have to wait here, rightoutside the bloody cop shop?

06:38.240 --> 06:40.040
Yes, because I'm too
bloody busy to traipse

06:40.160 --> 06:42.640
across town just so you cantell me you don't know nothing.

06:42.760 --> 06:45.120
Well, I know there's gonnabe marches all over town.

06:45.240 --> 06:46.800
I know.

06:46.920 --> 06:48.600
Now this place is a ghost shipbecause most of the bloody cops

06:48.720 --> 06:50.640
in West Auckland are beingsent into town in case you lot

06:50.760 --> 06:52.240
get difficult again.

06:52.360 --> 06:53.720
Jeez, they're evening
talking about me having

06:53.840 --> 06:54.680
to put on the uniform again.

06:54.800 --> 06:56.200
[chuckling]

06:56.320 --> 06:57.800
And if that happens,
Bert, the first person I

06:57.920 --> 07:00.600
hit with my baton will be you.

07:00.720 --> 07:03.760
Yeah, well, if they called offthe tour like they should have,

07:03.880 --> 07:05.400
none of you would
have to go anywhere.

07:05.520 --> 07:07.320
Thanks for thatstartling piece of insight.

07:07.440 --> 07:08.440
Look, I've gotta go.

07:08.560 --> 07:10.440
Phineas's mum passed away.

07:10.560 --> 07:11.360
Mammy's dead?

07:11.480 --> 07:14.120
That's what I said.

07:14.240 --> 07:15.760
And here I thought
her kind couldn't die.

07:15.880 --> 07:17.120
Catholics?

07:17.240 --> 07:19.440
At least something
like that, Bert.

07:19.560 --> 07:21.240
Jesus, Phineas must
be a bloody wreck.

07:26.320 --> 07:28.200
Hi, sweetheart.

07:28.320 --> 07:30.400
how are you?

07:30.520 --> 07:32.680
Phineas's brothers
and sister are here.

07:32.800 --> 07:34.560
They make me a bit nervous.

07:34.680 --> 07:36.960
And how's Phineas?

07:37.080 --> 07:38.840
He's gone very quiet.

07:38.960 --> 07:40.560
Hardly spoken since
he got the news.

07:40.680 --> 07:43.000
And he hasn't punched any walls.

07:43.120 --> 07:45.640
That's usually what he
does when he's upset.

07:45.760 --> 07:46.680
He fixes them after.

07:46.800 --> 07:48.800
He's real good at fixing walls.

07:48.920 --> 07:50.280
Well, his mammy
meant a lot to him.

07:50.400 --> 07:51.640
He's probably just in shock.

07:51.760 --> 07:53.120
I guess.

07:53.240 --> 07:55.400
And I know it's terrible
that she's dead,

07:55.520 --> 07:59.080
but why did the bitch
have to go and die now?

07:59.200 --> 08:00.120
Would there be a better time?

08:00.240 --> 08:01.600
Any time.

08:01.720 --> 08:06.240
Any time would be finewith me, but not this week.

08:06.360 --> 08:09.120
Carol had plans to
watch the royal wedding.

08:09.240 --> 08:12.280
I've been looking
forward to it all year.

08:12.400 --> 08:14.440
Trust mammy to ruin
my special day,

08:14.560 --> 08:17.920
like she ruined every otherday of my bloody life.

08:18.040 --> 08:20.960
And I'm so terrible
for even thinking it!

08:21.080 --> 08:24.560
Well, let's just try
and get through it, eh?

08:24.680 --> 08:27.120
You know, for Phineas.

08:27.240 --> 08:28.040
Come on, love.

08:41.320 --> 08:42.480
Three fucking hours.

08:42.600 --> 08:43.400
I know.

08:43.520 --> 08:45.040
Jesus.

08:45.160 --> 08:48.080
It's no wonder Catholics arebloody miserable all the time.

08:48.200 --> 08:49.640
No offense, Father.

08:49.760 --> 08:51.000
No, none taken.

08:51.120 --> 08:53.840
You're not born a Catholicto enjoy yourself.

08:53.960 --> 08:55.240
I don't suppose I
could trouble you?

08:55.360 --> 08:57.080
Yeah.

08:57.200 --> 08:58.440
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

08:58.560 --> 08:59.760
Cheers.

08:59.880 --> 09:01.520
You're all friends
of Phineas, I take it?

09:01.640 --> 09:02.640
Yeah.

09:02.760 --> 09:03.800
And none of you
are of the faith?

09:03.920 --> 09:05.520
- Methodist.
- Dutch Reformed.

09:05.640 --> 09:06.960
- Atheist.
- Don't know.

09:07.080 --> 09:08.920
Yet, didn't I see youall come up for communion?

09:09.040 --> 09:09.920
I needed a drink.

09:10.040 --> 09:11.120
Yeah.

09:11.240 --> 09:12.680
- Chance to stretch the legs.- Yeah.

09:12.800 --> 09:14.360
The two hour barrier,
that can be a tough one

09:14.480 --> 09:16.000
for the uninitiated.

09:16.120 --> 09:18.000
And being an atheist, I don'tsuppose you worry that you'll

09:18.120 --> 09:19.600
be going to hell for that?

09:19.720 --> 09:22.360
I leave the likes of heavenand hell to you and Nora.

09:22.480 --> 09:24.680
Nora, bless her.

09:28.640 --> 09:32.600
Nora O'Driscoll, a
complicated woman.

09:32.720 --> 09:35.280
Difficult in life, but in death?

09:35.400 --> 09:36.760
Oh, dear.

09:36.880 --> 09:38.640
She'll be up there shoutingat St. Peter, will she?

09:38.760 --> 09:40.080
If he lets her in.

09:40.200 --> 09:41.600
That's probably why shewanted the extra prayers,

09:41.720 --> 09:43.640
that bloody woman!

09:43.760 --> 09:44.800
What's she done?

09:44.920 --> 09:46.800
Nora was always stirring.

09:46.920 --> 09:51.160
But now she's outdone herself.

09:51.280 --> 09:56.080
Would you say that Phineascan be a violent man?

09:56.200 --> 09:58.360
If the mood takes him?

09:58.480 --> 09:59.280
Uh.

09:59.400 --> 10:00.720
Yeah, absolutely.

10:00.840 --> 10:03.080
Bit of an
understatement, really.

10:03.200 --> 10:05.040
Are you sure?

10:05.160 --> 10:08.840
I mean, that's such ashame, isn't it, Phineas?

10:08.960 --> 10:12.520
But it was lovely to
see you all, wasn't it?

10:12.640 --> 10:14.280
Phineas, you need to
see your family out.

10:14.400 --> 10:17.400
Say goodbye to them, all right?

10:17.520 --> 10:18.360
I'll just pop this down.

10:18.480 --> 10:19.280
Come out and wave bye-bye.

10:22.320 --> 10:24.120
Patrick and Colleen and Shawnhave to go back to Marsden

10:24.240 --> 10:25.600
to milk the cows.

10:25.720 --> 10:27.160
Really?

10:27.280 --> 10:29.000
They couldn't find someoneelse to do that for one day?

10:29.120 --> 10:31.240
Also, I think Phineas iskind of freaking them out.

10:31.360 --> 10:32.520
I can relate to that.

10:32.640 --> 10:34.720
But you know what
this means, don't you?

10:34.840 --> 10:37.280
It means we could
still do the plan.

10:37.400 --> 10:38.200
Which plan is this?

10:38.320 --> 10:39.200
Our plan.

10:39.320 --> 10:41.600
Being there for Lady Di.

10:41.720 --> 10:43.680
I thought you shelvedthat plan when Mammy died.

10:43.800 --> 10:45.320
And now I'm unshelving it.

10:45.440 --> 10:46.680
Of course we can do it.

10:46.800 --> 10:48.520
Are we still doing the
dress part of the plan?

10:48.640 --> 10:50.160
Yes, the whole plan.

10:53.440 --> 10:54.680
Is Phin here?

10:54.800 --> 10:56.880
He's outside, saying
goodbye to his family.

10:57.000 --> 10:57.760
They've fled.

10:57.880 --> 10:59.200
Fled what?

10:59.320 --> 11:00.440
Nora said Phin was theonly one who didn't know.

11:00.560 --> 11:01.440
CAROL: Didn't know what?

11:01.560 --> 11:03.040
Oh, God, what's he doing here?

11:03.160 --> 11:06.120
That's some bloody nerve.

11:06.240 --> 11:07.320
What are you
doing here, Trotsky?

11:07.440 --> 11:09.560
No, I wanted to
come, pay my respects

11:09.680 --> 11:11.560
to Phineas on his loss.

11:11.680 --> 11:13.360
Didn't think you
liked Nora O'Driscoll.

11:13.480 --> 11:14.880
I wouldn't say I liked her.

11:15.000 --> 11:17.760
Bloody difficult woman tolike, but I respected her.

11:17.880 --> 11:19.240
I remember when I
was a constable,

11:19.360 --> 11:21.120
trying to arrest Phineasfor doing something stupid.

11:21.240 --> 11:22.480
Nora called me an
oppressor of the state

11:22.600 --> 11:23.640
and kicked me in the nuts.

11:23.760 --> 11:25.200
Well, she had
her good qualities.

11:25.320 --> 11:28.400
She was a small woman butwith the boot of Don Clark.

11:28.520 --> 11:29.520
Phineas is with his family.

11:29.640 --> 11:30.760
Yeah, I saw them outside.

11:30.880 --> 11:32.400
I'll catch him when
he comes back in.

11:32.520 --> 11:35.320
And in the meantime, I mightjust grab myself a curried egg.

11:35.440 --> 11:36.400
Yeah, that's right.

11:36.520 --> 11:39.160
Get your snout in the trough.

11:39.280 --> 11:41.280
Good sendoff, was it?

11:41.400 --> 11:43.600
Long, but the--
the hymns were nice.

11:43.720 --> 11:46.200
I very much enjoyed meetingup with you on Saturday.

11:46.320 --> 11:48.520
You might want to avoid
the devils on horseback.

11:48.640 --> 11:50.840
Carol can't make anythingshe doesn't burn.

11:50.960 --> 11:52.760
In fact, I can't
stop thinking about it.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.200
Hello, hello, hello.

11:54.320 --> 11:56.200
Here for the free food, are you?

11:56.320 --> 11:59.280
I might just check
on the sausage rolls.

11:59.400 --> 12:02.080
I think there's pork on
the sausage rolls, Mike.

12:02.200 --> 12:03.720
Would that be cannibalismfor your kind?

12:03.840 --> 12:04.680
Funny, Lefty.

12:04.800 --> 12:05.640
Never heard that one before.

12:09.200 --> 12:10.600
Oh, have they gone already?

12:10.720 --> 12:12.000
That was quick.

12:12.120 --> 12:13.520
How are you, soldier?

12:13.640 --> 12:16.200
Father Murphy, uh, just wantsto have a word with you.

12:16.320 --> 12:17.120
Something about your mammy.

12:20.840 --> 12:24.640
This is all a bitbloody awkward, isn't it?

12:24.760 --> 12:25.720
Do you need money?

12:25.840 --> 12:27.000
No.

12:27.120 --> 12:28.960
No, your sister made
a generous donation

12:29.080 --> 12:31.400
to the church restoration fund.

12:31.520 --> 12:32.320
Bless her.

12:35.240 --> 12:36.680
Shall we get on
with it, Father?

12:36.800 --> 12:37.600
God save me.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.840
As you know, I spent a lot oftime with your dear mother.

12:43.960 --> 12:46.800
She really liked
your weekly visits.

12:46.920 --> 12:49.080
Used to get real angry
when you missed one.

12:49.200 --> 12:51.600
Yes, she did.

12:51.720 --> 12:55.040
Anyway, on one of our
visits, um, your mother

12:55.160 --> 13:00.480
gave me this letter andasked me to give it to you

13:00.600 --> 13:02.280
in the event of her death.

13:02.400 --> 13:03.320
This is her will?

13:03.440 --> 13:04.320
No, it's not her will.

13:07.800 --> 13:08.960
- Is this about her house?- No.

13:09.080 --> 13:09.840
A bequest?

13:09.960 --> 13:12.760
No, you need to--

13:12.880 --> 13:13.760
the lad can read, right?

13:13.880 --> 13:15.120
Of course, I can bloody read!

13:15.240 --> 13:16.480
Just a bit difficult right now!

13:16.600 --> 13:19.040
True, she-- she had
an old fashioned hand.

13:19.160 --> 13:21.320
Maybe I could try.

13:21.440 --> 13:22.240
Thanks, Ted.

13:27.360 --> 13:32.440
"My dear son, it's playedin my mind for many years,

13:32.560 --> 13:34.800
that I haven't beenentirely honest with you."

13:39.920 --> 13:41.400
I'm thinking we kick
out the stragglers,

13:41.520 --> 13:43.480
then get our frocks
on and meet at yours.

13:43.600 --> 13:45.120
We have to do the frocks?

13:45.240 --> 13:49.040
Yes, so we're there with LadyDi, in our dresses, in support.

13:49.160 --> 13:50.360
It's like Phineas
and the All-Blacks.

13:50.480 --> 13:52.560
They can't win if
he's not watching.

13:52.680 --> 13:53.840
[screaming]

13:53.960 --> 13:54.760
Phineas.

13:54.880 --> 13:56.560
He's punched something.

13:56.680 --> 13:57.600
[screaming]

13:57.720 --> 13:58.480
And some more things.

13:58.600 --> 14:00.480
Fuck!

14:00.600 --> 14:01.960
Phin?

14:02.080 --> 14:02.960
Phineas?

14:03.080 --> 14:03.840
What the hell?

14:07.040 --> 14:08.960
Phineas?

14:09.080 --> 14:09.880
Phin?

14:17.000 --> 14:17.800
Phineas?

14:20.920 --> 14:22.080
I'll be on my way.

14:22.200 --> 14:24.720
God be with you.

14:24.840 --> 14:25.600
Phineas is gone.

14:25.720 --> 14:27.560
What just happened?

14:27.680 --> 14:31.080
