Murphy's wise,

16:51.840 --> 16:52.840
he'll be a long way from here.

16:52.960 --> 16:53.880
And very drunk.

16:54.000 --> 16:56.160
He made her write that letter.

16:56.280 --> 16:57.760
No, he didn't.

16:57.880 --> 16:59.120
Why would he do that?

16:59.240 --> 17:00.640
Fucking church are real
fucking sneaky like that

17:00.760 --> 17:02.000
sometimes.

17:02.120 --> 17:03.120
Phineas, your mother
wrote the letter, OK?

17:03.240 --> 17:04.040
It's all true.

17:04.160 --> 17:05.560
No, it's not!

17:05.680 --> 17:08.840
Open up, open up, open up!

17:11.840 --> 17:13.120
- Hey, come on, mate.
- Open up!

17:13.240 --> 17:14.400
I know you're in there!

17:14.520 --> 17:17.400
Look, Phineas, we
know that you're angry.

17:17.520 --> 17:24.160
Maybe if we all just go get adrink, you know, talk about it?

17:27.040 --> 17:28.840
Yeah, a drink would be good.

17:28.960 --> 17:31.520
That's the spirit.

17:31.640 --> 17:32.440
Come on, mate.

17:36.760 --> 17:37.640
Wow.

17:37.760 --> 17:38.640
It still fits?

17:38.760 --> 17:39.600
Mostly.

17:39.720 --> 17:41.680
Some places are a bit snug.

17:41.800 --> 17:42.960
You should get
changed into yours.

17:45.680 --> 17:46.640
Well, that works.

17:46.760 --> 17:47.800
Have you found him?

17:47.920 --> 17:48.920
They're bringing him in now.

17:49.040 --> 17:49.840
Thank God for that.

17:49.960 --> 17:51.040
In a manner of speaking.

17:51.160 --> 17:52.240
What's this fancy dress now?

17:52.360 --> 17:53.640
It's my wedding dress.

17:53.760 --> 17:56.000
Or, it will be, when I
get all the way into it.

17:56.120 --> 17:57.320
Let me.

17:57.440 --> 17:58.440
Thanks.

17:58.560 --> 17:59.560
Also lovely.

18:02.640 --> 18:04.920
Hello, sweetheart.

18:05.040 --> 18:05.800
You look beautiful.

18:05.920 --> 18:06.760
Baby.

18:06.880 --> 18:07.840
Don't touch me.

18:07.960 --> 18:08.760
Why?

18:08.880 --> 18:10.960
What have I done?

18:11.080 --> 18:12.240
Why did you marry me?

18:12.360 --> 18:13.520
Because I love you.

18:13.640 --> 18:14.920
It's all a bloody
sham, though, isn't it?

18:15.040 --> 18:16.200
- OK, uh--
- Hey?

18:16.320 --> 18:17.400
Phin-- Phin just
needs a beer, so, uh,

18:17.520 --> 18:18.520
let's take it downstairs, eh?

18:18.640 --> 18:20.560
Great idea.

18:20.680 --> 18:21.680
Didn't know you
still had that.

18:21.800 --> 18:23.120
Yet, here it is.

18:23.240 --> 18:24.520
Still got the legs for it.

18:24.640 --> 18:26.840
Should I come?

18:26.960 --> 18:29.800
Uh, probably better ifyou just give us a minute.

18:29.920 --> 18:31.720
You ladies are looking lovely.
- Thanks.

18:31.840 --> 18:34.880
You should get your
wedding dress on.

18:35.000 --> 18:37.480
I would, but I don't
actually have one.

18:37.600 --> 18:39.160
Oh, my God.

18:39.280 --> 18:40.520
I'm so sorry.

18:40.640 --> 18:42.200
I never would havesuggested it if I'd known.

18:42.320 --> 18:43.480
Known what?
Nothing to know.

18:43.600 --> 18:44.360
Who needs a gin.

18:44.480 --> 18:45.800
Me, easy on the tonic.

18:50.000 --> 18:51.320
All good here, love?

18:51.440 --> 18:52.840
Yeah, box of fluffies.

18:52.960 --> 18:54.320
You can go and look
after the real disaster.

19:02.920 --> 19:03.720
Read 'em and weep, boys!

19:07.000 --> 19:08.000
We got a game going.

19:08.120 --> 19:08.920
Too bad.

19:09.040 --> 19:10.280
Scoot.

19:10.400 --> 19:11.760
You can't tell me to
scoot from my own house.

19:11.880 --> 19:14.600
But I can, 'cause it'smy house, and I pay for it.

19:14.720 --> 19:16.600
Bugger off somewhere else.

19:16.720 --> 19:19.440
Out!

19:19.560 --> 19:21.920
Fascist.

19:22.040 --> 19:25.000
I want to offer my condolenceson the passing of your mother.

19:25.120 --> 19:26.520
You didn't even
know my mother.

19:26.640 --> 19:29.240
But I hear she was awoman of faith and virtue.

19:29.360 --> 19:31.720
And the Bible tells us agood woman is above rubies.

19:31.840 --> 19:33.600
And it's a lovely thought,Falani, but off you go, eh?

19:36.320 --> 19:38.760
Here you go, mate.

19:38.880 --> 19:41.240
Righto, should be
safe down here.

19:41.360 --> 19:42.760
Not a bouquet in sight.

19:42.880 --> 19:45.080
A-bloody-men to that.

19:45.200 --> 19:47.920
NEWSCASTER [ON TV]: What agreat day, not just for Britain,

19:48.040 --> 19:49.760
but for the whole commonwealth.

19:49.880 --> 19:52.720
Mrs. Carol, you
are truly beautiful.

19:52.840 --> 19:54.200
Don't be silly.

19:54.320 --> 19:56.400
You're a vision ofloveliness, all that is pure.

19:56.520 --> 19:57.280
Stop being a girl.

19:57.400 --> 19:58.240
Don't be late.

19:58.360 --> 19:59.680
Don't get into trouble.

19:59.800 --> 20:01.280
Oh, my God.

20:01.400 --> 20:02.560
Do you think when
Phin looks at me,

20:02.680 --> 20:04.840
he'll see his mother,
what his Mammy did

20:04.960 --> 20:07.600
with that Maori battalionguy is, you know,

20:07.720 --> 20:09.400
like what I did with Falani.

20:09.520 --> 20:10.920
You headed away with that boy?

20:11.040 --> 20:11.880
Once.

20:12.000 --> 20:14.040
I was drunk and lonely.

20:14.160 --> 20:16.080
Maybe Mammy was
drunk and lonely.

20:16.200 --> 20:17.480
She did like to drink.

20:17.600 --> 20:19.160
A lot.

20:19.280 --> 20:21.960
Carol, Phineas will not thinkthat, unless you bring it up.

20:22.080 --> 20:23.080
I won't bring it up, then.

20:23.200 --> 20:23.960
Good idea.

20:27.120 --> 20:28.840
NEWSCASTER [ON TV]: And acheer goes up from the crowd.

20:28.960 --> 20:30.720
I guess this
proves it's my fault.

20:30.840 --> 20:31.960
What's your fault?

20:32.080 --> 20:33.680
Why I haven't
given him children.

20:33.800 --> 20:34.840
He's Maori, right?

20:34.960 --> 20:36.280
And they have heaps of children.

20:36.400 --> 20:37.960
They certainly do.

20:38.080 --> 20:42.680
Carol, nothing is your fault.Let's just watch the wedding.

20:42.800 --> 20:44.800
Rita, I don't want
to be a stickybeak,

20:44.920 --> 20:48.960
but why didn't you have a dress?

20:49.080 --> 20:51.720
It didn't seem
important at the time.

20:51.840 --> 20:53.960
No one got invited
to their wedding.

20:54.080 --> 20:56.000
Not even you and Lefty?

20:56.120 --> 20:57.480
No.

20:57.600 --> 20:58.960
But I thought you twowere really good friends.

20:59.080 --> 21:00.680
We knew each other socially.

21:00.800 --> 21:02.480
Went to the some dances,
that kind of thing.

21:02.600 --> 21:03.960
Next thing, they were married.

21:04.080 --> 21:05.400
How long were you engaged?

21:05.520 --> 21:08.200
There wasn't any time,and we didn't wanna wait.

21:08.320 --> 21:09.080
God, that's so romantic.

21:11.960 --> 21:13.680
It wasn't a shotgun
wedding, was it?

21:13.800 --> 21:14.560
No, no.

21:14.680 --> 21:18.080
Wolf came later.

21:18.200 --> 21:20.720
This was more of
a Luger wedding.

21:20.840 --> 21:22.160
A what?

21:22.280 --> 21:23.960
Du kleine Schlampe!

21:24.080 --> 21:25.520
I'm not gonna
listen to you anymore!

21:25.640 --> 21:26.480
He is dirt.

21:26.600 --> 21:27.400
He's a thief!

21:27.520 --> 21:28.320
I love him!

21:28.440 --> 21:29.680
He's a criminal!

21:29.800 --> 21:32.840
I am gonna marry Ted,
and you cannot stop me!

21:32.960 --> 21:34.120
- I will kill you first.
- No.

21:34.240 --> 21:35.000
Fuck you.

21:35.120 --> 21:35.920
Slut!

21:38.520 --> 21:39.400
No!

21:39.520 --> 21:40.320
She's here.

21:40.440 --> 21:41.360
She's here.

21:44.800 --> 21:45.840
Look at her.

21:45.960 --> 21:46.960
It's like a great,
big blancmange.

21:47.080 --> 21:48.280
No, it's not.

21:48.400 --> 21:49.840
It's beautiful.
- Look at the train.

21:49.960 --> 21:51.200
It's all creased.

21:51.320 --> 21:52.560
CAROL: Do you expect her
to carry a bloody iron?

21:52.680 --> 21:53.920
I'm just making a comment.

21:54.040 --> 21:56.720
Stop ruining the wedding!

21:56.840 --> 21:58.480
NEWSCASTER [ON TV]: Trulya dress fit for a princess.

21:58.600 --> 21:59.680
You hear from
Des when that South

21:59.800 --> 22:01.040
African money's showing up?

22:01.160 --> 22:01.920
No, not yet.

22:05.680 --> 22:06.520
You all right, mate?

22:06.640 --> 22:07.440
I don't know.

22:12.280 --> 22:15.280
I-- I don't know
who I am anymore.

22:15.400 --> 22:16.840
Oh, come off it.

22:16.960 --> 22:18.680
You're the same bloke
you always were.

22:18.800 --> 22:20.600
We don't hold that
cop shit against you.

22:20.720 --> 22:22.680
I can't be a Maori.

22:22.800 --> 22:24.600
I mean, I'm not
lazy or a bludger.

22:24.720 --> 22:25.720
No offense, Bert.

22:25.840 --> 22:26.840
Hey, look,
there's worse things

22:26.960 --> 22:28.160
you could be than a Maori.

22:28.280 --> 22:30.560
Like one of them racist
South African bastards.

22:30.680 --> 22:31.480
Or a faggot.

22:31.600 --> 22:32.960
Who you calling a faggot?

22:33.080 --> 22:35.600
No, no one's callinganyone a faggot, all right?

22:35.720 --> 22:36.920
Your dad was Maori battalion.

22:37.040 --> 22:38.360
You know, those guys
were great fighters.

22:38.480 --> 22:39.680
I'm not a Maori.

22:39.800 --> 22:41.280
What's so wrong
with being a Maori?

22:41.400 --> 22:43.560
You end up on the
dole, or in prison.

22:43.680 --> 22:44.960
There are some
successful Maoris.

22:45.080 --> 22:45.880
Like who?

22:49.160 --> 22:51.040
The bloke in Parliament,uh, Winston what's his handle.

